&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Staff Nurse - Queen Mary&#39;s Hospital SW15&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to give outstanding care every time? Do you want to feel really proud of where you work? If you want to consistently deliver the fundamentals of patient care and ensure that improvements we make are sustained in the long term, then we want to work with you. We have opportunities for Registered Nurses to join us on;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mary Seacole, &lt;/strong&gt; a 42 bedded ward specialising in Senior Health / Rehabilitation. It’s based at &lt;strong&gt;Queen Mary’s Hospital in Roehampton&lt;/strong&gt; - a newly built community hospital offering state of the art rehabilitation services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer preceptorship, mentorship, rotations and professional development to ensure you get the very best from your time with us. With a variety of career progression opportunities - from Clinical Ward Manager, Practice Educator, Matron, Nurse Practitioner and Clinical Nurse Specialist roles. Where do you see yourself?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jenny Furber - Leech - Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;jenny.leech@stgeorges.nhs.uk - 020 8487 6135&lt;/p&gt;
